STEP 1: Hadoop Core Components
- Storage System: HDFS (Hadoop Distributed File System) - stores data across cluster nodes
- Resource Manager: YARN centralizes cluster resource allocation & scheduling for multiple apps
STEP 2: MapReduce Workflow Components
- Mapper: Parallel task that processes input splits and emits key-value pairs from raw data
- Combiner: Optional "mini-reducer" on mapper node that pre-aggregates data to reduce network traffic
- Shuffle: Phase that moves/sorts mapper output by key and sends it to appropriate reducer nodes
- Reducer: Aggregates/combines all values for each key from mapper output to produce final result
- Replication: HDFS copies data blocks (default 3x) across nodes for fault tolerance

STEP 3: SPARK
Q1 Apache Spark-- distributed in-memory computing engine for large-scale data processing across clusters.

Spark Driver (Master) → Manages everything, creates partitions
Spark Executor (Worker) → Each partition processes alone on executor
  
-DATA COMES IN:--------100 Zomato servers receiving 1 crore orders per day (10GB data)
  
-Spark Driver (master node) does the partitioning based on input file size/splits 
  (default 128MB per partition) or based on user-specified numPartitions.
  -PARTITION = Data split into chunks across servers (1 crore orders → 200 partitions sample example)

"NARROW = Each partition is processed independently on ONE executor, NO data shuffle between partitions → FAST"  
    (map, filter, union)

"WIDE = Partitions exchange data ACROSS executors via network (group by, join) → SLOW due to SHUFFLE"
  (group, join, sort, distinct)
  
"ACTION = Spark waits to run ALL transformations until an ACTION is called (count, show, collect) 
  → This is LAZY EVALUATION"  
  
- RDD: Resilient Distributed Dataset - 
  immutable, fault-tolerant collection of objects partitioned across cluster

Resilient   = Can recover from failures (recomputes lost partitions)
Immutable   = Cannot change once created (new RDD on transformation)
Fault-tolerant = Rebuilds lost data using lineage (DAG)
Partitioned = Split into chunks across cluster
  
