【WHAT OPTIMIZER DOES - Example】

Query: Filter(age > 18) → Join(orders) → Select(name)

RDD (No Optimization):
  1. Join ALL data (1 billion records)
  2. Filter age > 18
  3. Select name
  Result: Huge join first → VERY SLOW

DataFrame (Catalyst Optimizer):
  1. Filter age > 18 FIRST (reduces data 90%)
  2. Join only filtered data (100 million records)
  3. Select name
  Result: 10x faster automatically

 RDD vs Dataset: RDD = JVM objects, no compile-time safety; Dataset = type-safe, combines RDD + DataFrame benefits

TRNASFORMATION= Lazy operation that creates NEW RDD/DataFrame from existing one (no execution)


【3 KEY POINTS】
1. LAZY - Doesn't run immediately
2. IMMUTABLE - Returns new, original unchanged  
3. NO RESULT - Returns RDD, not actual data
【ULTRA SHORT - One line each】
NARROW = NO shuffle, each works alone → FAST
WIDE = YES shuffle, data moves → SLOW  
ACTION = TRIGGERS execution → without it nothing runs

